This paper deals with constructing knowledge bases using probabilistic modeling and neural networks, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with data management and modeling, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB). The paper's focus on precision and attribute prediction suggests that it may also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
